    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2681: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hendaye</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-19T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >August 19, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 19—9:19
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. At meeting called by Argentine Ambassador to consider mediation, the subject
                    not mentioned because of general objections. Some talk about trying to arrange
                    exchange of prisoners but nothing done. Did not attend. San Sebastián bombarded
                    from air yesterday and many civilians including children and old men killed. In
                    accordance with warning given, to my personal knowledge reprisals will be taken
                    on certain number of political prisoners. Among prisoners there is Count
                    Romanones. San Sebastián apparently not demoralized by raid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
